cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a likely category as Horn description logics are used in ontology-mediated query answering, which is a common task in AI.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper deals with definability and expressive completeness results for Horn description logics.
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possibility as ontology-mediated query answering is also relevant to digital libraries.
- cs.LG (Learning) is a possibility as model comparison games can be seen as a type of game-theoretic learning.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the computational complexity of checking indistinguishability of models in Horn description logics.
